-- Ampal Rises Most in Almost a Week After U.S. Shares Surge
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-01-15T15:12:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/ampal-rises-most-in-almost-a-week-after-its-u-s-shares-surge.html
Ampal-American Israel (AMPL)  Corp. rose the
most in almost a week following an advance by the company’s
U.S.-traded shares.  The  shares of Ampal , the owner a 12.5 percent stake in a
company that exports gas from Egypt to Israel, gained 4.6
percent, the most since Jan. 10, to 1.546 shekels, or the
equivalent of $0.40, at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Ampal’s
U.S.-traded stock surged 15 percent in New York to $0.4276 on
Jan. 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
